com.tomtom.speedtools.mongodb.migratedb

Class MongoDBMigration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.mongodb.migratedb.MongoDBMigration

  • public class MongoDBMigration
extends Object
    This class defines a MongoDB migration from 1 version to another. By default, its migration path is the identity transformation, which effectively only changes the database version number in the 'migrator' collection.

      • getSingleValue

        @Nullable
protected <T> T getSingleValue(@Nonnull
                                         Class<T> resultClass,
                                         @Nonnull
                                         com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                                         @Nonnull
                                         String fieldPath)
        Reads a single value from property denoted by the fieldPath. The value in the property must have a class (derived from) resultClass. If not, a problem will be added, and null will be returned. If more than one value is found, a problem will also be added, and null will be returned. If the path cannot be traversed (because a property is missing), null is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The expected type of the value.
        Parameters:
        resultClass - The class the value should be assignable from.
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPath from.
        fieldPath - The path to the value that should be retrieved.
        Returns:
        The value, or null in case of errors.

      • getValues

        @Nonnull
protected <T> Iterable<T> getValues(@Nonnull
                                             Class<T> resultClass,
                                             @Nonnull
                                             com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                                             @Nonnull
                                             String... fieldPaths)
        Reads values from one or more properties reachable from object by traversing the given fieldPaths. These values should be assignable from the class resultClass. If a value is not, the value is skipped, and a problem is added. If the path cannot be traversed (because a property is not available) it will be skipped.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The expected type of the value.
        Parameters:
        resultClass - The class the values should be assignable from.
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPaths from.
        fieldPaths - The paths to the values that should be retrieved.
        Returns:
        An iterable with values of type T.

      • setValue

        protected void setValue(@Nonnull
                        com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                        @Nonnull
                        String fieldPath,
                        @Nullable
                        Object toValue)
        Sets the value at fieldPath to toValue. If the base path (i.e., the path before the last '.') cannot be resolved, the value is not set. If any of the segments of the path refers to a collection field, all objects contained are traversed, potentially resulting in multiple fields that will be set.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPath from.
        fieldPath - The path to the value to set.
        toValue - The value to set.

      • replaceValue

        protected void replaceValue(@Nonnull
                            com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                            @Nonnull
                            String fieldPath,
                            @Nullable
                            Object fromValue,
                            @Nullable
                            Object toValue)
        Replaces the value fromValue at path fieldPath with toValue. If the path cannot be resolved nothing is replaced. If any of the segments of the path refers to a collection field, all objects contained are traversed, potentially resulting in multiple values that will be replaced.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPath from.
        fieldPath - The path to the value to replace.
        fromValue - The value to replace.
        toValue - The value to replace with.

      • setDefault

        protected void setDefault(@Nonnull
                          com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                          @Nonnull
                          String fieldPath,
                          @Nullable
                          Object toValue)
        Sets the value toValue at path fieldPath when it does not already have a value. If the fieldPath cannot be resolved, no changes are made. If any of the segments of the path refers to a collection field, all objects contained are traversed, potentially resulting in multiple fields that will be set.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPath from.
        fieldPath - The path to the value to set.
        toValue - The value to set.

      • convert

        protected void convert(@Nonnull
                       com.mongodb.DBObject object,
                       @Nonnull
                       String fieldPath,
                       boolean createChildContext,
                       @Nonnull
                       MongoDBMigration.Converter<?> converter)
        Convert the values referred to by (object, fieldPath) using the given MongoDBMigration.Converter.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to start evaluating the fieldPath from.
        fieldPath - The path to the values to convert.
        createChildContext - If true, the created MongoDBMigration.Values will be added to the parent context. The consequence of this is that the converter is then able to use MongoDBMigration-methods that are dependent on this context (any of the getters that work with Values internally, such as getSingleValue(Class, DBObject, String)).
        converter - The converter to convert the values with.
